 U Thant, 1961\u20131971 |publisher=Scarecrow Press |location=Metuchen, N.J |year=2001 |isbn=0-8108-3700-5}}\n* {{cite book |author=Ramses Nassif |title=U Thant in New York, 1961\u20131971: A Portrait of the Third UN Secretary-General |publisher=St. Martin's Press |location=New York |year=1988 |isbn=0-312-02117-8 |url=https://archive.org/details/uthantinnewyork100nass}}\n* Hanwong, L. (2014). \u02bb\u016a than nai th\u0101na l\u0113kh\u0101thik\u0101n \u02bbOngk\u0101n Sahaprach\u0101ch\u0101t ch\u0101o \u02bb\u0112ch\u012ba khon r\u01e3k [U Thant as the first Asian secretary-general of the United Nations]. In A. Khamson, T. Weerakietsoontorn & C. Khuntong (Eds.), ''Y\u014d\u031cn phinit ph\u016bs\u0101ng prawattis\u0101t \u02bb\u0112ch\u012ba Tawan\u02bb\u014d\u031ck Ch\u012bang Tai'' [Reflections on Makers of Southeast Asian History 2] (pp. 131\u201363). Bangkok: Reviews of Southeast Asian History and Culture Project (TRF). (in Thai)\n* {{cite book |author=U Thant |title=View from the UN |publisher=Doubleday |location=Garden City, NY |year=1978 |isbn=0-385-11541-5 |url=https://archive.org/details/viewfromun00utha_0}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n{{Commons category|U Thant}}\n* [https://www.un.org/av/photo/subjects/sg3.htm UN Photos of U Thant] from the United Nations website\n* [https://www.un.org/sg/en/content/u-thant Official UNSG biography] from the United Nations website\n\n{{-}}\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-dip}}\n{{s-bef |before=[[Dag Hammarskj\u00f6ld]] ({{flagicon|Sweden}})}}\n{{s-ttl |title={{flagicon|UN}} [[Secretary-General of the United Nations]] |years=November 1961 \u2013 December 1971}}\n{{s-aft |after=[[Kurt Waldheim]] ({{flagicon|Austria}})}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{-}}\n{{United Nations}}\n{{LN and UN Secretaries-General}}\n{{Gandhi Peace Award laureates}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Thant, U}}\n[[Category:1909 births]]\n[[Category:1974 deaths]]\n[[Category:Amateur radio people]]\n[[Category:Burmese diplomats]]\n[[Category:Burmese people of W